t 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">held to account the public service broadcasters, the BBC and Channel 4 in hearings on their annual reports and other matters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">examined the work of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the regulators Ofcom and the G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ambling Commission;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conducted pre-legislative scrutiny of three draft Public Bodies Orders and the draft Gambling (Licensing and Advertising) Bill, publishing our reports in time for the House and other committees to take into account the evidence we had received and the conclusions we had reached</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conducted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> post-legislative assessment of the Gambling Act 2005</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">held major inquiries into supporting the creative economy and into library closure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">questioned the Department’s record on broadband delivery and the future </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the Science Museum Group;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">consider</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed issues of public concern such as racism in football, press regulation, nuisance calls and online safety</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 100.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">followed up the unsatisfactory response given to us by the football authorities in relation to football governance. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">As recommended by the Liaison Committee, we have tried to keep our reports short and accessible, deviating from this only when the inquiries themselves have thrown up multiple, complex issues which have to be addressed fully.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We are also trying to ensure that our range of witnesses is as diverse and inclusive as possible.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Because of our remit, we have found no difficulties in provoking media interest in our work. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There are two areas in which we have encountered obstacles to the discharge of our remit.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">First, we are still awaiting publication of the Department’s Annual Report and Accounts for 2012–13. We intend to hold an evidence session with the Secretary of State and Permanent Secretary of the Department when these are published. We are aware that the Department requested extra time to produce the Report and Accounts given the disruption to normal departmental activity caused by the Olympics and the technical challenges produced by various machinery of government/public body changes. However, the continuing failure to publish these vital documents seriously compromises our—and the House’s—ability to hold Ministers to account for the work of this department.  </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">While following up our long-term work on press regulation, we decided it would be appropriate to take oral evidence from Lord Justice Leveson about the implementation of the recommendations arising from the inquiry he led into the culture, practices and ethics of the press. However, the Lord Chief Justice expressed concerns that an evidence session with the committee would involve a member of the judiciary in what was in effect a political discussion. He argued that Lord Justice Leveson chaired the inquiry as a sitting judge, and, as a sitting judge, he would be unable to comment on his conclusions or on subsequent events. We took the view that Lord Justice Leveson did not chair the inquiry as a judge: his judicial qualities may have made him an appropriate person to hear long and complex evidence and reach conclusions, but he was exercising generic attributes rather than acting in a judicial capacity. After long discussions which culminated in a formal letter requesting that he appear before the Committee, Sir Brian gave evidence in October 2013.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We comment on this matter as we think our experience raises issues which the Liaison Committee should consider. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">8 November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">  2nd Report of Session 2012–13</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">, HC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> 697</span></p></body></html>